## 📋 Overview

This project demonstrates end-to-end automation of cloud infrastructure deployments on Microsoft Azure. Rather than relying on manual Azure portal configuration — which is slow, error-prone, and impossible to audit — this project implements scripted, repeatable, and version-controlled deployment workflows using Azure CLI, PowerShell, and ARM template principles.

Automation is the defining skill that separates a junior cloud user from a mid-level cloud engineer. Anyone can click through a portal. Not everyone can write the script that provisions the same environment 100 times with zero configuration drift.

This project proves that capability.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- Replace manual portal-based deployments with scripted, repeatable workflows
- Enforce security controls (NSGs, RBAC) automatically at deployment time
- Eliminate configuration drift across cloud environments
- Build audit-ready infrastructure with version-controlled deployment records
- Demonstrate Infrastructure as Code (IaC) principles aligned with AZ-104 objectives

