## 📋 Key Steps Completed

### Step 1 — Environment Setup & Authentication
- Configured Azure CLI with authenticated session using `az login`
- Set active subscription to target deployment environment
- Established consistent naming conventions and variable structure for all scripts

### Step 2 — Automated Resource Group Provisioning
- Scripted resource group creation with standardized naming and location parameters
- Applied resource tags automatically at creation time for billing and governance tracking
- Validated resource group existence before deployment to prevent duplicate creation errors

### Step 3 — Virtual Network & Subnet Automation
- Automated VNet creation with defined address space using Azure CLI
- Scripted subnet configuration within the VNet for logical network segmentation
- Applied consistent network architecture across deployments without manual portal steps

### Step 4 — Network Security Group (NSG) Automation
- Scripted NSG creation and rule definition in a single deployment pass
- Automated inbound/outbound security rules — allowing only required ports and denying all others by default
- Attached NSG to subnet automatically — ensuring every VM deployed into the network inherits security rules

### Step 5 — Virtual Machine Deployment via Script
- Automated VM provisioning including compute size, OS image, admin credentials, and network attachment
- Eliminated manual portal configuration — entire VM environment provisioned from a single script execution
- Validated successful deployment programmatically before proceeding to access control configuration

### Step 6 — Automated RBAC Assignment
- Scripted role assignments scoped to the resource group level
- Applied least-privilege principles — roles assigned only for what the deployment requires
- Automated access control eliminates the human error risk of manual permission configuration

### Step 7 — Repeatable Deployment Workflow
- Parameterized all scripts for reuse across different environments (dev, test, production)
- Built idempotent deployment logic — scripts can run multiple times without creating duplicate or conflicting resources
- Documented all deployment steps in version-controlled format for full auditability

### Step 8 — Automated Resource Cleanup
- Built teardown scripts to delete all provisioned resources after lab completion
- Automated cleanup prevents orphaned resources and eliminates unnecessary Azure costs
- Validates complete resource removal programmatically after teardown

